ly 2.9% + $.30 per transaction</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - Attendees redirected to Google Checkout website for payment</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - Receive funds immediately into Google Checkout account</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Authorize.net</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - Fee: varies</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - Use your existing merchant account</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - To activate, call: 888.541.9753</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> Click <a href=\"/en_us/t/how-will-i-be-paid\">here </a>to see how to select a payment processor in Eventbrite. And to learn how to offer your attendees offline (non-credit-card) payment options, click <a href=\"/en_us/t/offline-payment-options\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229650', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('74', '9', 'When do I get paid?', 'when-do-i-get-paid-', '<div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>When do I get paid?</h3>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>View the status of your payout after your event</li>\r\n                                <li>Reissue a \"returned\" direct deposit or bank transfer</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"alert alert-block\">\r\n                            Are you using our new design to create or edit your events?\r\n                            <a href=\"#newcreate\"> Jump to new help </a>\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                or <a href=\"#\"> Learn more </a>\r\n                            </span>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> Payouts are generally sent 5 business days after your event ends, and take a number of days to reach you.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    The end date of your event is set in <strong>Step 4: Add When</strong> on the <strong>Edit </strong>page for your event, and is not necessarily the same as your ticket sales end date, which is set in <strong>Step 2: Add Ticket Information</strong> on the <strong>Edit</strong> page.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    From the <strong>My Events</strong> page, click on the title of your event to go to the Event Summary on the <strong>Manage </strong>page.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/manage.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you see an alert in your <strong>Total Sales</strong> box asking you to update your payment information, you need to enter how you\'d like to receive your funds.<strong> </strong>You can click the <strong>update your payment information</strong> link to do this, or click <a href=\"/en_us/t/how-will-i-be-paid\">here </a>for more detailed instructions.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img  src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/updatepayment.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    24 or more hours after your event has ended, you will see the <strong>Payment Status</strong> box in your <strong>Event Summary</strong>, which will show the status of your payout.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/paymentstatus2.JPG\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - A status of <strong>Processing</strong> means that we are batching and delivering the direct deposit request to our bank or printing and posting the check.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - The&nbsp;<strong>Initiated</strong> status usually only appears briefly for direct deposit (bank transfer) payments, and means that the funds are in the process of being moved to your bank.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - A status of <strong>Sent</strong> will show 5 days after the end of your event, and means that we\'ve sent your payout. (Remember that your payout isn\'t sent to you until 5 days after the end of the event.)\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -----\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>US AND CANADIAN ACCOUNTS</strong>\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For US and Canadian accounts, you should receive your check within 5 business days--or your direct deposit within 2 business days--from the&nbsp;<strong>Date of Payment</strong> displayed (or from the next business day, if the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> falls on a weekend or US banking holiday).\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>ACCOUNTS IN ALL OTHER COUNTRIES</strong>\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For accounts in other countries, you should receive your bank transfer within 4 business days from the&nbsp;<strong>Date of Payment&nbsp;</strong>displayed (or the next business day, if the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> falls on a weekend or US banking holiday).\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    In general, this means that you should receive the funds into your bank account 5-10 business days after the end of your event. Please keep in mind that the delivery of your funds may be delayed by banking holidays in the country where your bank is located.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -----\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"<?php echo Yii::app()->request->baseUrl; ?>/images/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\">\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>For direct deposits and bank transfers, the actual amount of time for the funds to post to your account after the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> displayed can vary, depending on your bank. The time frames shown above are for general guidance only.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - A <strong>Returned </strong>status means that we attempted to send your payment, but either the check was returned to us or the bank transfer did not complete. Click the link to update and save your payment information.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/reenter.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Then click on the green <strong>Reissue</strong> button back on the <strong>Event Summary</strong> page to reissue your payout, which will be processed and sent the following business day.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/reissue.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"block-step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                                <h3>What is the status of the payout for my event?</h3>\r\n                                <ul>\r\n                                    <li>View the status of your payout after your event</li>\r\n                                    <li>Reissue a \"returned\" direct deposit or bank transfer</li>\r\n                                </ul>\r\n                            </div>\r\n\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> Payouts are generally issued 5 business days after your event ends, and take a number of days to reach you.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    The end date of your event is set in <strong>Step 1: Add your Event Details</strong> on the <strong>Event Details </strong>page for your event. (This date isn\'t necessarily the same as your ticket sales end date, which is set in <strong>Step 2: Create Tickets</strong> your event\'s <strong>Event Details</strong> page.)\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To see the status of your event’s payout, you’ll need to go to the <strong>Event Summary</strong> screen, found on your event’s <strong>Manage </strong>page. To get there, click <strong>My Events</strong> at the top of the screen, and then click on the name of your event.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"611\" height=\"248\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/manage1.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    24 or more hours after your event has ended, you will see the <strong>Payment Status</strong> box in your <strong>Event Summary</strong>, which will show the status of your payment.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"606\" height=\"346\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/status.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - A status of <strong>Processing</strong> means that we are batching and delivering the direct deposit request to our bank or printing and posting the check.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - The <strong>Initiated</strong> status usually only appears briefly for direct deposit (bank transfer) payments, and means that the funds are in the process of being moved to your bank.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    - A status of <strong>Sent</strong> will show 5 days after the end of your event, and means that we\'ve sent your payout. (Remember that your payout isn\'t sent to you until 5 days after the end of the event.)</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -----</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>US AND CANADIAN ACCOUNTS</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For US and Canadian accounts, you should receive your check within 5 business days--or your direct deposit within 2 business days--from the&nbsp;<strong>Date of Payment</strong> displayed (or from the next business day, if the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> falls on a weekend or US banking holiday).</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>ACCOUNTS IN ALL OTHER COUNTRIES</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For accounts in other countries, you should receive your bank transfer within 4 business days from the&nbsp;<strong>Date of Payment&nbsp;</strong>displayed (or the next business day, if the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> falls on a weekend or US banking holiday).</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    In general, this means that you should receive the funds into your bank account 5-10 business days after the end of your event. Please keep in mind that the delivery of your funds may be delayed by banking holidays in the country where your bank is located.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -----</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"<?php echo Yii::app()->request->baseUrl; ?>/images/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\">\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>For direct deposits and bank transfers, the actual amount of time for the funds to post to your account after the <strong>Date of Payment</strong> displayed can vary, depending on your bank. The time frames shown above are for general guidance only.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n                                    - A <strong>Returned </strong>status means that we attempted to send your payment, but either the check was returned to us or the bank transfer did not complete. You can easily correct your information and then automatically reissue payout! First click the link to update and save your payment information.</p>\r\n                                <p style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n                                    <img width=\"613\" height=\"137\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/reenter.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n                                    Then click the green <strong>Reissue</strong> button back on the <strong>Event Summary</strong> page to reissue your payout. Your payout will be processed and sent the following business day!</p>\r\n                                <p style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n                                    <img width=\"613\" height=\"238\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/viewing-payout-status/reissue.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\">\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>If you don’t see a <strong>Payment Status </strong>box on your <strong>Event Summary </strong>page and do see an alert in your <strong>Total Sales</strong> box asking you to update your payment information, that means you need to enter how you\'d like to receive your funds.<strong> </strong>You can click the <strong>update your payment information</strong> link to do this, or click <a href=\"/en_us/t/how-will-i-be-paid\">here </a>for more detailed instructions.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Once you enter and save your payment information, we can get you your payout as scheduled!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>', '1349229655', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('75', '9', 'Non-profit program', 'non-profit-program', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Non-profit program</h3>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                For more information on Eventbrite for Causes, go <a href=\"#\">here</a>!\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                     \r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229660', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('76', '9', 'Fee-handling options', 'fee-handling-options', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Fee-handling options</h3>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    Attendees pay fees by default (fees added to price)</li>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    Choose to pay fees yourself instead (fees included in price)</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"alert alert-block\">\r\n                            Are you using our new design to create or edit your events?\r\n                            <a href=\"#newcreate\"> Jump to new help </a>\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                or <a href=\"#\"> Learn more </a>\r\n                            </span>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> This tutorial covers how to select who&mdash;you, the organizer, or your attendees&mdash;pays the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees/\">fees</a> for your paid event. By default, the fees are added to the ticket price so that your attendees pay all fees, though you can change this, as detailed below.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Remember, though, that Eventbrite is free to use if your event free!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    From the <strong>My Events</strong> page, click on <strong>Edit </strong>next to the name of an event to go to that event\'s <strong>Edit </strong>page. (If you are setting up a new event page--that is, you just pressed <strong>Create Event</strong> and the page you are on says <strong>Create an Event</strong>--you can skip this step and go directly to the second part of step 2 below.)</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"617\" height=\"342\" border=\"0\" title=\"How to create ticket types\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/edit.png\" alt=\"How to create ticket types\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    In <strong>Step 2: Add Ticket Information</strong>, click on the name of the ticket type (in blue) to bring up the <strong>Edit Ticket</strong> window for that ticket type.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"617\" height=\"222\" border=\"0\" title=\"How to create ticket types\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/step%202.png\" alt=\"How to create ticket types\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you are setting up a new event page, and so are on the <strong>Create an Event </strong>page, click <strong>Create a Ticket</strong>, fill out the name, price and quantity available of that ticket type, and then continue to step 3 below.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/create%20ticket.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    &nbsp;</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Near the bottom of the <strong>Edit Ticket</strong> window, click <strong>Show</strong> next to <strong>Advanced Options</strong> to display more options. You will find the <strong>Service Fee</strong> options near the bottom of the expanded window. (If you have previously viewed the Advanced Options, you will not need to click <strong>Show</strong>, as the expanded window will automatically display.)</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"616\" height=\"310\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/edit%20ticket.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"615\" height=\"684\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/advanced%20options.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    There are three options from which you can choose regarding who pays the fees for your event. They are as follows:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>ADD fees on top of total ticket price</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This means that your attendees will pay all fees.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -You, the organizer, will receive the entire price of each ticket, as the attendees will pay all fees.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This is the default option.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -Here is how your event page would display for a $20 ticket with this option selected:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"617\" height=\"124\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/add%20fees.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>INCLUDE fees into total ticket price</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This means that you will pay all fees.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -You, the organizer, will receive the price of each ticket, minus the fees.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This is the recommended option for <a href=\"/en_us/t/collect-donations\">donation</a> ticket types.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -Here is how your event page would display for a $20 ticket with this option selected:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"616\" height=\"127\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/include%20fees.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>INCLUDE credit card processing fee in the total ticket price and ADD the Eventbrite fee on top of total ticket price</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This is an option only if you choose credit card processing for your event.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -This means that you will pay the credit card processing fee, and your attendees will pay the Eventbrite fee.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    -Here is how your event page would display for a $20 ticket with this option selected:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"614\" height=\"123\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/split%20fees.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                &nbsp;</p>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>If you have selected PayPal or Google Checkout to process your credit card payments, you cannot pass along to your attendees the processing fee that they charge, unfortunately. You can, however, choose for your attendees to pay the Eventbrite fee, by choosing to <strong>ADD fees into total ticket price</strong>, as detailed above.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                5</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Once you make your selection, be sure to click <strong>Save</strong> to save your changes and to go to the <strong>Edit</strong> page for your event.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To see how the fees will display to your attendees, click <strong>View </strong>(or <strong>Preview</strong> if you haven\'t yet published your event) in the upper left of the <strong>Edit</strong> page to check out your event page in a new browser tab/window.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"617\" height=\"407\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/view.png\" alt=\"How to collect donations on the event page\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                &nbsp;</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"block-step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                                <h3>How to decide who pays the fees</h3>\r\n                                <ul>\r\n                                    <li>\r\n                                        Attendees pay fees by default (fees added to price)</li>\r\n                                    <li>\r\n                                        Choose to pay fees yourself instead (fees included in price)</li>\r\n                                </ul>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> This tutorial covers how to select who&mdash;you, the organizer, or your attendees&mdash;pays the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees/\">fees</a> for your paid event. By default, the fees are added to the ticket price so that your attendees pay all fees, though you can change this, as detailed below. Remember, though, that Eventbrite is free to use if your event is free!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To get started, first <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/signup\">sign up</a> for a free Eventbrite account or <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/login\">log in</a> to your existing Eventbrite account and <a href=\"/en_us/t/event-page-creation\">create an event</a>.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you’d like to edit an already-created event, click <strong>My Events</strong> at the top of the screen and then, click on <strong>Edit </strong>to the right of your event’s name.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"608\" height=\"220\" border=\"0\" title=\"How to create ticket types\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/feehandle_1b.png\" alt=\"How to create ticket types\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Go to <strong>Step 2:</strong> <strong>Create Tickets</strong>. Use the <strong>Global Service Fee </strong>tool to make the same selection for all types of tickets for this event.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"609\" height=\"251\" border=\"0\" title=\"How to create ticket types\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/feehandle_2b.png\" alt=\"How to create ticket types\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you would like to choose who pays the fees on a per-ticket basis, select <strong>Customize per ticket type</strong> and/or click on the <strong>Settings</strong> for a ticket type and make your selection in the <strong>Service Fees</strong> section.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"610\" height=\"310\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/feehandle_3.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note:</strong> Click <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees/\">here</a> to see more information about Eventbrite\'s fees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    By default, <strong>Pass on fees to the buyer</strong> will be selected, meaning that the fees will be added on to the ticket price and paid by the buyer. You, the organizer, will receive the entire price of each ticket.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Here’s how your event page would display for a $20 ticket with this option selected:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"516\" height=\"254\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/feehandle_4.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you choose <strong>Absorb the fees</strong>, the buyer will pay just the price of the ticket and the fees will be deducted from that price. You, the organizer, will receive the price of each ticket, minus the fees. This is the recommended option for <a href=\"/en_us/t/collect-donations\">donation</a> ticket types.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Here’s how your event page would display for a $20 ticket with this option selected:</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"521\" height=\"245\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/fee-handling-options/fees3b.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong> If you have <a href=\"/en_us/t/payment-processor-options\">selected</a> PayPal or Google Checkout to process your credit card payments, you unfortunately cannot pass the processing fee that PayPal or Google Checkout charges along to your attendees. You can, however, choose for your attendees to pay the Eventbrite fee, by choosing to <strong>Pass on fees to the buyer</strong>, as detailed above.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Once you make your selection, be sure to click <strong>Save</strong> to save your changes.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To see how the fees will display to your attendees, click <strong>Colors &amp; Options</strong> in the upper left to take a look at your event page!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229664', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('77', '9', 'Credit card processing FAQ', 'credit-card-processing-faq', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Credit card processing FAQ</h3>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>For step-by-step instructions on setting up credit card processing for your event, go <a href=\"/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-setup\">here</a>. And if your tickets are priced in a currency other than U.S. dollars, click <a href=\"/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-faq-for-nonusd-events\">here</a> for more information.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How much does it cost to use credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    By default, we charge a small fee to your customers, or you can choose to <a href=\"/en_us/t/feehandling-options\"> absorb this fee yourself</a>. The credit card processing fee is 3.0%, and the Eventbrite fee is 2.5% + $0.99.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    So, if you use credit card processing, the total cost to your attendee (or to you, if you <a href=\"/en_us/t/feehandling-options\">choose</a>) is 5.5% per ticket + $0.99. (Example: $50 ticket + $3.74 fee = $53.74 total).</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How do I receive my money if I use credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After your event, Eventbrite will send you a confirmation email with the details of your event revenue and payout information.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    You have 96 hours (four days) from the end of your event to process any <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">refunds </a>and make any adjustments. On the fifth business day after the end date of your event, Eventbrite will mail you a check (for events with US dollar-denominated tickets only) or issue a direct deposit for your total event revenue (less Eventbrite and credit card processing fees).</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Direct deposits can take up to two business days to appear in your account after the payout is initiated, depending on your bank; checks generally arrive within five business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>If the fifth day after the end date of your event falls on a weekend or a US banking holiday, the payout will be initiated on the next business day.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>Eventbrite is currently only able to process credit card payouts to banks located in a country that uses the currency in which you priced your tickets on Eventbrite. (For instance, if your tickets are priced in US dollars, you will only be able to receive a US dollar-denominated payout, sent to a bank located in the United States.) If you wish to receive payout in a different currency or to a bank located in a different country, please select a <a href=\"/en_us/t/payment-processor-options\">different payment processor</a> for your event.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Can I get an example or two of when I might receive my money for a direct deposit?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For example, if your event ends on a Sunday (1/8), your event payout will be issued on the following Friday (1/13), five days after your event ends. If you\'ve chosen to receive a direct deposit, your funds should arrive in your bank account account by the end of Tuesday (1/17), two business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    As another example, if your event ends on a Monday (1/9), your event payout will be issued on the following Monday (1/16). (Since the fifth day after your event ends is a Saturday (1/14), payout is initiated the next business day, which is Monday (1/16).) If you\'ve chosen to receive a direct deposit, your funds should arrive in your bank account by the end of Wednesday (1/18), two business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Can I change the payment processing method at any time?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After ticket sales have started for an event, you cannot change the payment processing method. However, you can change it at any time during the setup of your event, and you can use a different method for each event you host. Learn more about how to change your payment processing method <a href=\"/en_us/t/how-will-i-be-paid\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                5</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How are refunds processed with credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    You can refund your guests directly through your Eventbrite account, as long as the payout for your event has not yet been processed and sent by us. &nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Find step-by-step instructions on how to process refunds <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229669', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('78', '9', 'Credit card processing FAQ for non-USD events', 'credit-card-processing-faq-for-non-usd-events', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Credit card processing FAQ for non-USD events</h3>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>For step-by-step instructions on setting up credit card processing for your event, go <a href=\"/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-setup\">here</a>. If your tickets are priced in U.S. dollars, click <a href=\"/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-faq\">here</a> for more information.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How much does it cost to use credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    By default, we charge a small fee to your customers, or you can choose to <a href=\"/en_us/t/feehandling-options\">absorb this fee yourself</a>. The credit card processing fee for non-USD events is 3.5%, which is in addition to the <a href=\"/en_us/t/fees-in-all-supported-currencies\">Eventbrite fee</a>. Here is the Eventbrite fee for tickets priced in currencies other than U.S. dollars:</p>\r\n                                <center>\r\n                                    <table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 376px; height: 125px;\" class=\"intl-table\">\r\n                                        <tbody>\r\n                                            <tr class=\"tablehead\">\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    <strong>Currency</strong></td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    <strong>Fee</strong></td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    <strong>Max Fee</strong></td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                            <tr>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    Euros</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    2.5% + €0.75</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    €7.50</td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                            <tr>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    Pounds Sterling</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    2.5% + £0.65</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    £6.50</td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                            <tr>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    Australian Dollars</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    2.5% + AU$0.99</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    AU$9.95</td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                            <tr>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    Canadian Dollars</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    2.5% + C$0.99</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    C$9.95</td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                            <tr>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    New Zealand Dollars</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    2.5% + NZ$1.50</td>\r\n                                                <td>\r\n                                                    C$15.00</td>\r\n                                            </tr>\r\n                                        </tbody>\r\n                                    </table>\r\n                                </center>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <br>\r\n                                    So, to recap, if you use credit card processing, the total per-ticket cost to your attendee (or to you, if you so <a href=\"/en_us/t/feehandling-options\">choose</a>) is 3.5% + the Eventbrite fee for your particular currency.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>We regret that currently we cannot issue payouts to banks located in Italy or Portugal, though we\'re actively working to provide this level of support in the future. In the meantime, we suggest&nbsp;<a href=\"/en_us/t/use-paypal-to-process-orders\">PayPal</a> as an alternative to Eventbrite\'s credit card processing.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How do I receive my money if I use credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After your event, Eventbrite will send you a confirmation email with the details of your event revenue and payout information.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    You have 96 hours (four days) from the end of your event to process any <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">refunds </a>and make any adjustments. On the fifth business day after the end date of your event, Eventbrite will mail you a check (for USD events only) or issue a direct deposit for your total event revenue (less Eventbrite and credit card processing fees).</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Direct deposits can take up to two business days to appear in your account after the payout is initiated, depending on your bank; checks generally arrive within five business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>If the fifth day after the end date of your event falls on a weekend or a US banking holiday, the payout will be initiated on the next business day.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note: </strong>Eventbrite is currently only able to process credit card payouts to banks located in a country that uses the currency in which you priced your tickets on Eventbrite. (For instance, if your tickets are priced in US dollars, you will only be able to receive a USD-denominated payout, sent to a bank located in the United States.) If you wish to receive payout in a different currency or to a bank located in a different country, please select a <a href=\"/en_us/t/payment-processor-options\">different payment processor</a> for your event.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Can I get an example or two of when I might receive my money for a direct deposit?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    For example, if your event ends on a Sunday (1/8), your event payout will be issued on the following Friday (1/13), five days after your event ends. If you\'ve chosen to receive a direct deposit, your funds should arrive in your bank account account by the end of Tuesday (1/17), two business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    As another example, if your event ends on a Monday (1/9), your event payout will be issued on the following Monday (1/16). (Since the fifth day after your event ends is a Saturday (1/14), payout is initiated the next business day, which is Monday (1/16).) If you\'ve chosen to receive a direct deposit, your funds should arrive in your bank account by the end of Wednesday (1/18), two business days after the payout is initiated.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Can I change the payment processing method at any time?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After ticket sales have started on an event, you cannot change the payment processing method. However, you can change it at any time during the setup of your event, and you can use a different method for each event you host. Learn more about how to change your payment processing method <a href=\"t/edit-payment-options\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                5</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>How are refunds processed with credit card processing?</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    You can refund your guests directly through your Eventbrite account, as long as the payout for your event has not yet been processed and sent by us.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Find step-by-step instructions on how to process refunds <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                &nbsp;</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Tip:</strong> For more information, you can visit our fees page <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229676', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('79', '9', 'Credit card processing setup', 'credit-card-processing-setup', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Credit card processing setup </h3>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    Easiest way to accept credit card payments</li>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    Highest purchase conversion rate for attendee</li>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    Overview of setup and payout processes</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"alert alert-block\">\r\n                            Are you using our new design to create or edit your events?\r\n                            <a href=\"#newcreate\"> Jump to new help </a>\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                or <a href=\"#\"> Learn more </a>\r\n                            </span>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To get started, first <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/signup\">sign up</a> for a free Eventbrite account or<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/login\"> log in</a> to your existing Eventbrite account and<a href=\"/en_us/t/event-page-creation\"> create an event</a>.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you’d like to edit an already-created event, click <strong>My Events</strong> at the top of the screen and then click on <strong>Edit </strong>to the right of your event’s name.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"608\" height=\"268\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/2edit22.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    In <strong>Step 2: Add Ticket Information</strong>, click on <strong>Edit</strong> in the <strong>Collect Payments</strong> section.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"606\" height=\"250\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/collectpayments1.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    In the&nbsp;<strong>Payment Options</strong> window, select<strong> Credit Card Processing</strong>. Then choose whether you\'d like to receive the payout for your event in the form of a <strong>check </strong>(available only for USD-denominated events) or a <strong>direct deposit</strong>. Finally, enter the mailing address (for a check) or bank account information where you\'d like your payout delivered.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Make sure to click <strong>Save</strong> when you\'re finished!</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"611\" height=\"812\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/2dd2.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>You\'re all set!</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    When attendees register for your event, they\'ll enter their billing information on the checkout page for your event and answer any <a href=\"/en_us/t/custom-questions-for-attendees\">custom questions</a> you\'ve created before finalizing their order. That\'s it!</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"593\" height=\"969\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/2register2.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                5</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After your event, Eventbrite will send you a confirmation email with the details of your event revenue and payout information. You have 96 hours (4 days) from the end of your event to process any <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">refunds</a> and make any adjustments.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                6</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    On the 5th business day after your event has ended, Eventbrite will mail you a check (available only for USD-denominated events) or issue you a direct deposit for your total event revenue (less Eventbrite and credit card processing <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees/\">fees</a>). It\'s really that easy!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note:</strong> For more information about credit card processing, please go <a href=\"https://eventbrite.desk.com/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-faq\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <br>\r\n                                    <br>\r\n                                    &nbsp;</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"block-step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                                <h3>Credit card processing setup </h3>\r\n                                <ul>\r\n                                    <li>\r\n                                        Easiest way to accept credit card payments</li>\r\n                                    <li>\r\n                                        Highest purchase conversion rate for attendees</li>\r\n                                    <li>\r\n                                        Overview of setup and payout processes</li>\r\n                                </ul>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    To get started, first <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/signup\">sign up</a> for a free Eventbrite account or<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/login\"> log in</a> to your existing Eventbrite account and<a href=\"/en_us/t/event-page-creation\"> create an event</a>. Once you click <strong>Make Event Live</strong> you\'ll be taken to your event\'s <strong>Manage</strong> page.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    If you’d like to edit an already-created event, go to your event\'s <strong>Manage</strong> page by clicking <strong>My Events</strong> at the top of the screen and then clicking on your event’s name.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"608\" height=\"270\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/manage2.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                2</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    On your event\'s&nbsp;<strong>Manage</strong> page, select&nbsp;<strong>Payment Options</strong> from the features menu on the left side of the page.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"230\" height=\"196\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/features.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                3</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Once you\'re on the <strong>Payment Options</strong> screen, select<strong> Credit Card Processing </strong>from the <strong>Select payment processor </strong>dropdown menu. Then choose whether you\'d like to receive the payout for your event in the form of a <strong>check </strong>(available only for USD-denominated events) or a <strong>direct deposit</strong> from the <strong>Payout </strong><strong>method</strong> dropdown menu.</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    Finally, enter the mailing address (for a check) or bank account information where you\'d like your payout delivered. Make sure to click <strong>Save Changes</strong> when you\'re finished!</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"607\" height=\"523\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/paymentoptions.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                4</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>You\'re all set!</strong></p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    When attendees register for your event, they\'ll enter their billing information on the checkout page for your event and answer any <a href=\"/en_us/t/custom-questions-for-attendees\">custom questions</a> you\'ve created before finalizing their order. That\'s it!</p>\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <img width=\"593\" height=\"969\" src=\"http://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/tutorials/payment_processing/2register2.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                5</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    After your event, Eventbrite will send you a confirmation email with the details of your event revenue and payout information. You have 96 hours (4 days) from the end of your event to process any <a href=\"/en_us/t/refund-an-order\">refunds</a> and make any adjustments.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                6</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    On the 5th business day after your event has ended, Eventbrite will mail you a check (available only for USD-denominated events) or issue you a direct deposit for your total event revenue (less Eventbrite and credit card processing <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/fees/\">fees</a>). It\'s really that easy!</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                <img src=\"http://ebmedia.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/static/images/en_US/helpcenter/article_note.png\" alt=\"Note\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>Note:</strong> For more information about credit card processing, please go <a href=\"/en_us/t/credit-card-processing-faq\">here</a>.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->', '1349229681', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `etk_faqs` VALUES ('80', '9', 'Fees in all supported currencies', 'fees-in-all-supported-currencies', '<!--CONTENT-->\r\n                        <div class=\"block-heading\">\r\n                            <h3>Fees in all supported currencies</h3>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <br/>\r\n\r\n                        <!--step-->\r\n                        <div class=\"step\">\r\n                            <div class=\"stepnumber\">\r\n                                1</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"stepcontent\">\r\n                                <p>\r\n                                    <strong>What is the Eventbrite fee for all the currencies that you support?</strong></p>\r\n                                <table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 408px; height: 385px;\" class=\"intl-table\">\r\n                                    <tbody>\r\n                                        <tr class=\"tablehead\">\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                <strong>Currency</strong></td>\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                <strong>Eventbrite Fee</strong></td>\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                <strong>Max Eventbrite Fee</strong></td>\r\n                                        </tr>\r\n                                        <tr>\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                U.S. Dollars</td>\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                2.5% + $0.99</td>\r\n                                            <td>\r\n                                                $9.95</td>\r\n                                        </tr>\r\n                                        <tr>\r\n                                            <td>